abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Dec. 16--Jim Bunning, one of eight pitchers in the history of major league baseball to pitch a perfect game, was traded today by the Philadelphia Phillies  to the Pittsburgh Pirates for Woody Fryman, a left-handed pitcher and three minor league players.
